		<p>P. S. I suppose another cause for your<lb/> dislike <del>for</del> to lawyers is the fact that being six<lb/> months in arrears for rent of the &#34;Israelite Office&#34;<lb/> which you have now left&#44; the lawyers have been called in by your landlord<lb/> to aid in the collection of the rent&#44; &#38; if there<lb/> were no lawyers you would be &#34;benefited&#34; from<lb/> the effects of the law&#58; Very true &#38; very right Dr<lb/> but in this case &#34;justice will be <add>&#63;</add>cuted&#34;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I would like to know Revd Sir&#44; why<lb/> it was that <date>Saturday</date> the <date>Sabbath</date> of the Israelite<lb/> was the day set especially for the Rest to receive<lb/> a deputation of Israelites presenting a grievance<lb/> they desired to remedy which bore upon them as<lb/> Israelites&#59; verily the President &#38; his cabinet could<lb/> not have had a greater esteem for those who would<lb/> thus openly violate their <date>Sabbath</date> by attending<lb/> to secular political affairs&#58; No deputation<lb/> of Christians would have been received&#44; or would<lb/> have presented themselves on their day of rest.<lb/> But I suppose you were too elated with the<lb/> honors thrust upon you &#38; much too busy to think<lb/> of the day&#58;&#8212;</p>
          
